    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Treatment of cotton yarn or fabric by immersion in a caustic solution of sodium hydroxide or other chemical base. Fibers so treated swell permanently, and the cotton is made stronger and more lustrous. Named after Alexander Mercer (1791-1866), who perfected the process. </Note_Text>
